1) Method Overloading in Java

	- If a class has multiple methods having same name but different in parameters, it is known as Method Overloading.

2) 	Advantage of method overloading
		
	- Method overloading increases the readability of the program.

3) 	Different ways to overload the method

		- There are two ways to overload the method in java

			1) By changing number of arguments
			2) By changing the data type
			
4) Why Method Overloading is not possible by changing the return type of method only?
	
	- no possible  ,only because of ambiguity problem 

5) 	Can we overload java main() method?

	- Yes, by method overloading.
	  You can have any number of main methods in a class by method overloading. 
	  But JVM calls main() method which receives string array as arguments only. Let's see the simple example:		